Profile Summary

The Data Science Intern will be a fantastic opportunity for a student enrolled in an accredited program with the opportunity to work in a real-world, high-tech environment. The intern will participate with the team in:

Profile Description

Performing detailed analysis to deliver insight and support analytics initiatives;
Working closely with Predictive Analytics team and provide data analysis and support for modeling initiatives;
Business data analysis;
Data visualization and/or predictive modeling on one or more Voya business domains, such as end-customers, institutions, distribution, fraud, expenses, or web behaviors;
Supporting in-flight analytics use case projects, data exploration to evaluate ideas for new analytics use case opportunities;
Other ongoing data analytics work as needed.

Depending on the intern’s skills and time available, work may also include:

Work with Hadoop on Voya’s Big Data Platform;
Acquisition and assessment of publicly available data sources (e.g., data from the Federal Reserve, US Census, Data.gov, USPS, Zillow, etc).

Incoming Juniors, Seniors Or Graduate Students

Education and Experience:

Pursuing an undergraduate/grad degree in Data Analytics, Mathematics or related business discipline;
Minimum GPA of 3.5;
Not afraid of learning, providing feedback and to be given feedback on performance;
Detail oriented with good presentation skills;
Analytical capabilities – being able to see things differently than others with substance and relevance;
Available to work 40 hours/wk in the summer (10-12 Weeks)

Critical Skills

At Voya, we have identified the following critical skills which are key to success in our culture:
Customer Focused: Passionate drive to delight our customers and offer unique solutions that deliver on their expectations.
Critical Thinking: Thoughtful process of analyzing data and problem solving data to reach a well-reasoned solution.
Team Mentality: Partnering effectively to drive our culture and execute on our common goals.
Business Acumen: Appreciation and understanding of the financial services industry in order to make sound business decisions.
Learning Agility: Openness to new ways of thinking and acquiring new skills to retain a competitive advantage.
